#### Users
  - user_counts - The number of individual users that have enabled the beta feature. (If 1 user enabled the feature on 2 wikis they will be counted twice)
  - global_user_counts - The number of global users that have enabled the beta feature (If 1 user enabled the feature on 2 wikis they will be counted once)
  - global_disables - The number of global users that were using the feature yesterday, but have disabled it today.
  - global_enables - The number of global users that were not using the feature yesterday, but have enabled it today.

#### Events
  - hookinit - The number of times the JS has been added to a page by the PHP hook (excludes people with the BF or feature disabled)
  - load - The number of times the main slider JS has been loaded on a page (counted once per request).
  - lazyload - The number of times the lazy slider JS has been loaded on a page (counted once per request).
  - init - The number of times the slider has been started / rendered / expanded from its bar.
  - arrowClick - The number of times the arrow at either end of the slider is clicked.
  - pointerMove - The number of times a pointer is moved, either by dragging or by clicking on a revision bar.
  - historyChange - The number of times the browser back or forward buttons are used to navigate the slider.
  - expand - The number of times the container has been expanded
  - collapse - The number of times the container has been collapsed

#### Errors
  - init - Something went wrong when initially starting / rendering the slider
  - refresh - Something went wrong while reloading the diff after a new set of revisions was selected
  - outOfRange - LEGACY, Someone tried to load the slider on a diff which was outside of the most recent 500 revisions

#### Timing Names
  - Full load time - The time taken from the start of the slider render / build to the end when displayed to the user.
  - initFetchRevisionData - The ammount of time spent doing the API calls to get the revision data to be displayed.

#### Timing Values
  - Max / Upper - The maximum time in the given timeframe
  - Mean - The mean / average time in the given timeframe.
  - Median - The median / middle time in the given timeframe.
  - Min / Lower - The minimum time in the given timeframe.
  - p95 Max - The maximum time in the given timeframe for 95% of cases.
  - p75 Max - The maximum time in the given timeframe for 75% of cases.
